The EstNLTK package bundles the Vabamorf morphological analyzer
(https://github.com/Filosoft/vabamorf), which is dual-licensed under
the LGPL-2.1 and a separate commercial license. Users distributing
this server must comply with Vabamorf's license terms in addition to
this project's Apache-2.0 license.

POS tag inventory and morphological categories are produced by Vabamorf
and follow the conventions documented in EstNLTK.

This product bundles the Estonian Wordnet (estwn-et, version
estwn-et-2.7.0), used by the `synonyms` tool, distributed under the
Creative Commons Attribution-ShareAlike 4.0 license (CC-BY-SA-4.0).
The Estonian Wordnet is developed by the Institute of the Estonian
Language and obtained via the EstNLTK resource catalogue. estonian-mcp
also re-hosts an unmodified copy of this data as a GitHub Release
asset (wordnet_2026-02-13.zip) for build-time download resilience.
Anyone redistributing this data must preserve attribution and apply
CC-BY-SA-4.0 share-alike to it; the obligation applies to the Wordnet
data only, not to estonian-mcp's Apache-2.0 source code.

This product also bundles compressed Estonian fastText word embeddings
(file: /opt/models/fasttext-et-medium in the Docker image, ~33 MB,
100K vocab) used by find_related_words and check_compound_familiarity.
The underlying vectors are licensed under Creative Commons
Attribution-ShareAlike 3.0 (CC-BY-SA-3.0):

  Original vectors:
    Grave, E., Bojanowski, P., Gupta, P., Joulin, A., Mikolov, T.
    "Learning Word Vectors for 157 Languages." LREC 2018.
    https://fasttext.cc/docs/en/crawl-vectors.html

  Compression library:
    avidale/compress-fasttext.
    https://github.com/avidale/compress-fasttext

The compressed model file shipped here was built from cc.et.300.bin
(downloaded 2026-05-18) via compress-fasttext.prune_ft_freq with
new_vocab_size=100_000 and new_ngrams_size=200_000.

The bundled model file remains under CC-BY-SA-3.0 — anyone
redistributing this Docker image or any derivative model file must
preserve attribution and apply share-alike to derivative model files.
The rest of estonian-mcp (source code, server.py, etc.) stays under
Apache-2.0; the share-alike obligation applies only to the embeddings
file itself.

This product bundles a legal-Estonian collocation index
(data/legal_collocations.json.gz) used by the common_legal_usage tool.
The SHIPPED index contains only aggregate collocation/frequency
statistics (facts) distilled from PUBLIC-DOMAIN Riigi Teataja
legislation — currently the Law of Obligations Act (Võlaõigusseadus) —
fetched via scripts/fetch_riigiteataja.py and built with
scripts/build_legal_collocations.py. Estonian legislation is freely
reusable; the index is offered under Apache-2.0 with the rest of the
source, and no legislation text is redistributed (only statistics).
Coverage is broadened by adding more act ids.

The build script also supports a `--source hf` research mode over the
`paulpall/legalese-sentences_estonian` dataset (Estonian National
Corpus), which is licensed for NON-COMMERCIAL use only — an index
derived from it must NOT be shipped and is not distributed here.
